# 📌 Key Insights

- Nearly half of the patients are classified as pre-diabetic.
- Average hemoglobin levels differ naturally between males and females.
- Cholesterol levels remain within the normal range.
- Platelet counts are normal for the majority of patients.
- White Blood Cell counts indicate a generally healthy population.

---

# 💡 Recommendations

- Launch awareness programs for pre-diabetic patients.
- Improve screening for younger age groups.
- Monitor patients with low platelet counts.
- Continue periodic blood health monitoring.

---

# ⚠ Challenges

- Data cleaning.
- Handling missing values.
- Standardizing medical measurements.
- Creating accurate KPIs.
- Designing an interactive dashboard.

